<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-15T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1710: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina (<persName corresp="#p_WF1" type="from">White</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-15T11:00:00-04:00">April
                                        15, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 11:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>35. Your circular April 13, 6 p.m.; and my No. 34, April 12, 5
                                    p.m.<note n="98" xml:id="d134fn98">Latter not printed.</note>
                                Minister of Foreign Affairs informs me that he urged Paraguayan
                                Minister to abandon reservations and that the latter promised to
                                telegraph this to Asunción. He had also instructed <persName corresp="#p_EFA1">Espil</persName> to cooperate with neutrals in
                                Washington. While press has published telegrams no important
                                editorial comment.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_WF1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>